==English==

===Noun===
'''adapter''' or '''adaptor'''
# One that adapts, such as a device used to effect operative compatibility between different parts of one or more pieces of apparatus.
# ''Computer Science.'' A hardware device, such as a printed circuit board, that enables a personal computer to use additional peripheral devices or hardware.
{{wikipedia}}
# (''British'' etc) A [[device]] that permits two or three [[plug]]s to be used on one [[electrical]] [[power]] [[point]]; a device that allows one [[format]] of plug to be used with a different format of [[socket]].

